<h2>Specific climate indicators for June 2018</h2>
<br><br>
In most parts of Europe the number of cold days was lower than in the reference period 1981-2010 (Figure 3, middle panel). As 'cold' relates to the lowest 10 percentile range, the reference number of cold days is 3 (10% of the days in a month). Only in European Russia, Finland, Greece, Portugal and southern Spain it was colder than usual with more number of cold days and nights.
